@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Segmentation> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Segmentation> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Segmentation> ;
    narr:childCount "24"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "a969ea4727808de85f32b92cd43961bad7a2dbcf" ;
    narr:narration """Segmentation tracks a moving target market, not a settled one. The earliest validated frame was [developer-first ICP](narr:Obs_Segmentation_ICP) — 10-50 person dev shops at $X-50M revenue. By Mar 2026 a [SMB pivot](narr:Narrative_SMBPivot) surfaced — \"bigger market than devs\" — backed by a [consistent SMB beta cohort pattern](narr:Narrative_SycamoreCohortPattern) of owners training staff and automating marketing, with [hub deployment and HIPAA questions](narr:Obs_EarlyProspectHubDeployment) already live. The frame shifted again in late Mar–Apr toward expertise: [the target is the packaged expert](narr:Obs_ScarletTargetMarketQuote), engagement defined by [shape not org size](narr:Obs_EnterpriseShapeDefinition). May 18 brought the [two-subsegment ICP refinement](narr:Narrative_ICPRefinedTwoSubsegments) — functional volume across enterprise SaaS vendors and small professional practices — [explicitly excluding Fortune 500](narr:Position_ICPExcludesFortune500). Jun 2026 added three named ICP profiles: [mid-market software](narr:Position_ICPMidMarketSoftware), [bespoke consultancies](narr:Position_ICPBespokeConsultancies), and [individual whales](narr:Position_ICPIndividualWhales). A Jun 30 conversation introduced [transcript-rich research firms and compliance/audit](narr:Narrative_ExpertNetworkTranscriptMarket) as a structurally distinct candidate segment. Concrete beachheads include the [cash-pay NYC alternative-care wedge](narr:Narrative_WedgeCashPayNYC), [architecture teams](narr:Narrative_ArchitectureTeamsBeachhead), and [Series A operations personas](narr:Position_OperationsICP). The arc moves dev→SMB→expert-practice→transcript-market; no human has signed a final landing.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Alignment_TonyDualPurpose> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AdditiveVsIncremental> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ArchitectureTeamsBeachhead> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpansionTracks> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpertNetworkTranscriptMarket> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ICPRefinedTwoSubsegments> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_KnowledgeExtractionBeachhead> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SMBPivot> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SycamoreCohortPattern> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_WedgeCashPayNYC> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DavidMicroservicesBlindersQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DomainsNotRealQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EarlyProspectHubDeployment> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EnterpriseShapeDefinition> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NumbersWorkB2C> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletTargetMarketQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_Segmentation_ICP> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPBespokeConsultancies> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPExcludesFortune500> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPIndividualWhales> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPMidMarketSoftware> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPTwoSubsegmentPattern> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_OperationsICP> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMBBusinessPlan> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "SMB is a larger addressable market than developers; business plan and materials must reflect this pivot" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SMBPivot> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The target market is becoming an expert that currently packages their work in a static and bounded way." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletTargetMarketQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the engagement is actually the same shape, even though that's an organization of like 5 versus 150" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EnterpriseShapeDefinition> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "ICP isn't headcount, it's functional volume. Same shape across enterprise SaaS vendors (50-500 employees, [amount]-50M) and successful professional practices (5-30 employees, [amount]-10M). Explicitly excludes Fortune 500." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ICPRefinedTwoSubsegments> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "These segmented domains don't really exist in practice. You may have a strategist in the company, but they do product and they do sales, and they touch all this other stuff." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DomainsNotRealQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Think about the numbers though, right? The numbers really work. B2C. Because if we take theory that every single person is now their own team." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NumbersWorkB2C> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "anywhere there are already existing transcripts" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpertNetworkTranscriptMarket> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Cash-pay alternative care, NYC. Pelvic floor, pain, somatic, integrative." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_WedgeCashPayNYC> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "B2C individual volume as a viable path: Tony's numbers argument treats every person as their own team, a frame that sits orthogonally to the B2B expert-practice ICP that otherwise dominates." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NumbersWorkB2C> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Transcript-rich research firms (Third Bridge, Gartner, Forrester) and compliance/audit as a structurally distinct segment — not expert-practice, not SMB, but institutional transcript accumulation — introduced Jun 30 and not yet integrated into the main ICP frame." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpertNetworkTranscriptMarket> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Domain-segmented compiles rejected on principle: Scarlet's argument that humans don't live in single domains cuts against any ICP framing that slices by vertical or function." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DomainsNotRealQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Individual 'whales' (high-net-worth, famous authors) named as ICP Profile 3 alongside mid-market software and bespoke consultancies — a consumer-adjacent outlier that the SMB-to-enterprise arc doesn't cleanly absorb." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ICPIndividualWhales> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Developer-first origin (10-50 person dev shops) was the validated starting ICP and remains in the record as a superseded but not refuted frame." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_Segmentation_ICP> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Additive vs. incremental value diagnostic (May 22) is a segmentation-adjacent framework — it implies ICP should be filtered by whether the product enables the impossible, not just improves the existing — a qualification that could redraw segment boundaries." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AdditiveVsIncremental> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}